Key Financial Ratio  Edit 0 2â€¦
Key Financial Ratio: A key financial ratio is defined as a common relation between financial concepts.

For example, "working capital" is a key ratio and is defined as "us-gaap: Assets, Current" / "us-gaap: Liabilities, Current".

The following is a summary of key ratios:

Key Ratios
Profitability ratios
    Gross margin, Gross profit margin or Gross Profit Rate
    Operating margin
    Profit margin
    Return on Equity (ROE)
            NetIncomeLoss / Equity
        Return on Assets (ROA)
            NetIncomeLoss / Assets


Liquidity ratios

Activity ratios (Efficiency Ratios)
    Operating Performance
        Operating Profit
            Revenues - (CostOfRevenue + OperatingExpenses)
        Return on Equity (ROE)
            NetIncomeLoss / Equity
        Return on Sales (ROS)
            NetIncomeLoss / Revenues
        Return on Assets (ROA)
            NetIncomeLoss / Assets
        Sustainable Growth Rate (SGR)
            [(NetIncomeLoss / Revenues) * (1+((Assets - Equity) / Equity))] / [(1 / (Revenues / Assets))-(((NetIncomeLoss / Revenues) * (1+(((Assets - Equity) / Equity)))))]
        Inventory Days
            Inventory / (CostOfRevenue/365)

    Corporate Liquidity
        Current Ratio
            CurrentAssets / CurrentLiabilities
        Quick Ratio
            (CurrentAssets - inventory) / CurrentLiabilities
        Cash Ratio
            cash / current liabilities
        Working Capital to Sales
            (CurrentAssets - CurrentLiabilities) / Revenues

    Corporate Value
        Price to Earnings Ratio (PE)
            share price / earnings per share
        Debt to Asset Ratio
            Liabilities / Assets
        Dividend Payout Ratio
            dividends paid / earnings
    Investment Ratios
        //Operation Profit Margin
        //    OperatingIncomeLoss / Revenues
        Net Profit Margin
            NetIncomeLoss / Revenues








